Denmark Says EU Shouldn’t Enforce Bank Tax Alone, Borsen Says

-- B y   T a s n e e m   B r o g g e r
-- 
2011-10-21T06:25:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-21/denmark-says-eu-shouldn-t-enforce-bank-tax-alone-borsen-says.html
Danish Prime Minister Helle
Thorning-Schmidt doesn’t want the European Union to pursue a
bank tax on its own, arguing such a levy should be enforced
globally to be effective, according to the Copenhagen-based
Borsen newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tasneem Brogger in London at 
